# Padroes Express para Services

## Service Baseado em Classe

```typescript
export class RecursoService {
  constructor(private readonly repository: RecursoRepository) {}

  async findAll(filtros?: ListRecursoFiltros): Promise<Recurso[]> {
    return this.repository.findMany(filtros);
  }

  async findOne(id: string): Promise<Recurso> {
    const recurso = await this.repository.findById(id);
    if (!recurso) {
      throw new NotFoundError(`Recurso ${id} nao encontrado`);
    }
    return recurso;
  }

  async create(dados: CreateRecursoInput): Promise<Recurso> {
    return this.repository.create(dados);
  }

  async update(id: string, dados: UpdateRecursoInput): Promise<Recurso> {
    await this.findOne(id);
    return this.repository.update(id, dados);
  }

  async remove(id: string): Promise<void> {
    await this.findOne(id);
    await this.repository.delete(id);
  }
}
```

## Injecao Manual de Dependencias

```typescript
// Composicao na inicializacao
const db = new PrismaClient();
const recursoRepository = new PrismaRecursoRepository(db);
const recursoService = new RecursoService(recursoRepository);
const recursoRouter = createRecursoRouter(recursoService);

app.use('/api/recursos', recursoRouter);
```

## Padrao Repository

```typescript
// Interface
export interface RecursoRepository {
  findMany(filtros?: ListRecursoFiltros): Promise<Recurso[]>;
  findById(id: string): Promise<Recurso | null>;
  create(dados: CreateRecursoInput): Promise<Recurso>;
  update(id: string, dados: UpdateRecursoInput): Promise<Recurso>;
  delete(id: string): Promise<void>;
}

// Implementacao
export class PrismaRecursoRepository implements RecursoRepository {
  constructor(private readonly prisma: PrismaClient) {}

  async findById(id: string): Promise<Recurso | null> {
    return this.prisma.recurso.findUnique({ where: { id } });
  }
  // ...demais metodos
}
```

## Erros de Dominio

```typescript
export class NotFoundError extends Error {
  constructor(message: string) {
    super(message);
    this.name = 'NotFoundError';
  }
}

export class ValidationError extends Error {
  constructor(message: string) {
    super(message);
    this.name = 'ValidationError';
  }
}
```

## Convencoes
- Service recebe dependencias via construtor (sem decorators)
- Composicao manual na raiz da aplicacao (composition root)
- Interface de repositorio para desacoplamento
- Erros de dominio customizados (sem usar erros HTTP)
- Service nao conhece Express (sem req/res)
- Um service por dominio, metodos com responsabilidade unica
{{else}}
# Express Service Patterns

## Class-Based Service

```typescript
export class ResourceService {
  constructor(private readonly repository: ResourceRepository) {}

  async findAll(filters?: ListResourceFilters): Promise<Resource[]> {
    return this.repository.findMany(filters);
  }

  async findOne(id: string): Promise<Resource> {
    const resource = await this.repository.findById(id);
    if (!resource) {
      throw new NotFoundError(`Resource ${id} not found`);
    }
    return resource;
  }

  async create(data: CreateResourceInput): Promise<Resource> {
    return this.repository.create(data);
  }

  async update(id: string, data: UpdateResourceInput): Promise<Resource> {
    await this.findOne(id);
    return this.repository.update(id, data);
  }

  async remove(id: string): Promise<void> {
    await this.findOne(id);
    await this.repository.delete(id);
  }
}
```

## Manual Dependency Injection

```typescript
// Composition at startup
const db = new PrismaClient();
const resourceRepository = new PrismaResourceRepository(db);
const resourceService = new ResourceService(resourceRepository);
const resourceRouter = createResourceRouter(resourceService);

app.use('/api/resources', resourceRouter);
```

## Repository Pattern

```typescript
// Interface
export interface ResourceRepository {
  findMany(filters?: ListResourceFilters): Promise<Resource[]>;
  findById(id: string): Promise<Resource | null>;
  create(data: CreateResourceInput): Promise<Resource>;
  update(id: string, data: UpdateResourceInput): Promise<Resource>;
  delete(id: string): Promise<void>;
}

// Implementation
export class PrismaResourceRepository implements ResourceRepository {
  constructor(private readonly prisma: PrismaClient) {}

  async findById(id: string): Promise<Resource | null> {
    return this.prisma.resource.findUnique({ where: { id } });
  }
  // ...other methods
}
```

## Domain Errors

```typescript
export class NotFoundError extends Error {
  constructor(message: string) {
    super(message);
    this.name = 'NotFoundError';
  }
}

export class ValidationError extends Error {
  constructor(message: string) {
    super(message);
    this.name = 'ValidationError';
  }
}
```

## Conventions
- Service receives dependencies via constructor (no decorators)
- Manual composition at the application root (composition root)
- Repository interface for decoupling
- Custom domain errors (don't use HTTP errors)
- Service doesn't know Express (no req/res)
- One service per domain, single-responsibility methods
